<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Hungarian_language&amp;action=edit&amp;section=33" title="Edit section: References">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">References</span></h2>
<div class="references-small">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-0" title="">^</a></b> Lebedynsky, Iaroslav. <i>Les Nomades: Les peuples nomades de la steppe des origines aux invasions mongoles</i>. Paris: Errance, 2003: p. 191</li>
<li id="cite_note-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1" title="">^</a></b> Sugar, P.F..<i>A History of Hungary</i>. Bloomington, IN: Indiana University Press, 1996: p. 9</li>
<li id="cite_note-2"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2" title="">^</a></b> Maxwell, A.<i>Magyarization, Language Planning and Whorf: The word Uhor as a Case Study in Linguistic Relativism</i>Multilingua 23: 319, 2004.</li>
<li id="cite_note-3"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3" title="">^</a></b> Marcantonio, Angela. <i>The Uralic Language Family: Facts, Myths and Statistics</i>. Blackwell Publishing, 2002: p. 19</li>
